<TITLE> UK pledges Tk 900 cr for Char population </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 19 (bdnews24.com)--The UK will provide Bangladesh with a Tk 900 crore grant aimed at improving the livelihoods of people living in remote river and coastal island areas, also known as Chars. The fund will boost the extended phase of the Chars Livelihood Programme, according to a joint statement released Sunday by the UK Department for International Development (DFID) and the Economic Relations Division (ERD). UK international development secretary Douglas Alexander announced the move at the recent Labour Party Conference, the statement said. Alexander said soaring food prices badly affected those whose lives were dependent on the shifting sands of Bangladesh's rivers and coasts. Bangladesh hopes the additional funding will help the CLP run effectively till 2015. The current phase of the project is expected to end late 2009, or early 2010. Under the CLP, livelihood assets are transferred to the hardest-hit families, providing employment during lean periods such as Monga and improving flood pr
